                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Late nineteenth century–early twentieth century.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (strong scarlet)</seg>
                        <desc>Mediocre but regular. <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14757WaldaMikael">Walda Mikāʾel</persName> is mentioned as the scribe in numerous supplication formulas throughout the manuscript together with the monastic community, e.g., <locus target="#16rb #64rb #75rc"/>. 
                           He is explicitely mentioned as the scribe on <locus target="#174vc"/>.</desc>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለዓ፡ ዓለ፡</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡</expan> (e.g., <locus target="#13vc #64rb #66rc"/>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ሰላ፡</abbr> for <expan>ሰላም፡</expan> (e.g., <locus target="#118va #119rb #132ra"/>)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; names of the donors; a few lines in the incipit page of monthly readings alternating with black lines; two
                           initial lines of each sections of the texts; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; 
                           the word <foreign xml:lang="gez">salām</foreign> (e.g., <locus target="#18va #19rb #20rb"/>).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus from="160r" to="160v"/>
                           <desc type="CommemorativeNote">Commemorative note on ʾAbbā <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14780NabiyaLeul">Nabiya Lǝʿul</persName> (for  <date ref="ethiocal:Hamle20">20 Ḥamle</date>). The note mentions the visit of ʾAbbā <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14780NabiyaLeul">Nabiya Lǝʿul</persName> 
                              to Emperor <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs IV</persName> (r. <date from="1872" to="1889">1872–89</date>), who supported him in establishing a monastic community. </desc><q xml:lang="gez">
                              ወበዛቲ፡ ዕለት፡ አዕረፈ፡ አባ፡ ነቢየ፡ ልዑል፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/> ወቦአ፡ ኀበ፡ መፍቀሬ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ንጉሥ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/></q>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#187v"/>
                           <desc type="CommemorativeNote">Commemorative note on the consecration of the <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0105DD">church of ʾAbuna Zamikāʿel Aragāwi </placeName>(for <date ref="ethiocal:Nahase13">13 Naḥāse</date>). </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ወበዛቲ: ዕለት: ቅዳሴ: ቤተ: ክርስቲያኑ: ለአቡነ: አረጋዊ: <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/></q>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#215rc"/>
                           <desc type="GuestText"><title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4630Zaaqrabku">Za-ʾaqrabku māḫleta</title>. It is written in a secondary hand.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ዘአቅረብኩ፡ ማኅሌተ፡ አዘኪርየ፡ አእላፈ፡ እምእለ፡
                              ተጸምዱከ፡ ዘልፈ፡፡ ለለይትነበብ፡ ተወከፈ፡ ዘንዴትየ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ እንተ፡ ረሰይከ፡ እግዚኦ፡ ጸሪቀ፡ መበለት፡
                              ውኩፈ፡፡ እምእለ፡፡ አብኡ፡ ብዑላን፡ እምብዕሎሙ፡ ዘተርፈ። ነቢያት፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ወሐዋርያት፡ ንጹሐን፡ ሰማዕት፡
                              ወጻድቃን፡ ወመላእክት፡ ትጉሃን፡ ደናግል፡ ዓዲ፡ ወመነኮሳት፡ ኄራን፡ ባርኮ፡ ባርኩ፡ ጉባኤ፡ ዛቲ፡ መካን፡
                              እስከ፡ አረጋዊ፡ ልኂቅ፡ ወንዑስ፡ ሕፃን፡ ለዘጸሐፎ፡ በክርታስ፡ ወለዘአጽሐፎ፡ እንዘ፡ ይደርስ። ለዘአንበቦ፡
                              ወለዘተርጐሞ፡ በልሳን፡ ሐዲስ፡ ወለዘሰምዓ፡ ቃላቲሁ፡ በዕዝነ፡ መንፈስ፡ በጸሎተ፡ እሙ፡<hi rend="rubric">ማርያም፡</hi> ዓራቂተ፡
                              ኵሉ፡ እምባዕስ፡ ኅቡረ፡ ይምሐረነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ።
                           </q>
