               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0105DD">Dabra Dāmmo ʾAbuna ʾAragāwi</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1889" notAfter="1913">The late King <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs IV</persName> (r. <date from="1872" to="1889">1872–89</date>) and the late <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2012Arayas">ʾArʾaya Śǝllāse Yoḥannǝs</persName> are mentioned the supplication formulas
                        throughout the manuscript. Also, King <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">Mǝnilǝk</persName> (r. <date from="1889" to="1913">1889–1913</date>) is mentioned in the supplication formulas beginning from <locus target="#75rc"/> onwards. 
                        We may conjecture that at the time of preparing the manuscript <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs IV</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2012Arayas">ʾArʾaya Śǝllāse Yoḥannǝs</persName> had been dead because the supplications call for prayer for the soul of both of them. 
                        This is not the case with the supplications dedicated to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">Mǝnilǝk</persName>. 
                        <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14781GabraMikael">Gabra Mikāʾel</persName> and <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14782TawaldaMadhen">Tawalda Madḫǝn</persName> are mentioned in the supplication formulas throughout the manuscript. 
                        In some supplication formulas, <foreign xml:lang="gez">daqiqa māḫbar</foreign> ‘children of the community’, that is, the Dabra Dāmmo monks together with the scribe <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14757WaldaMikael">Walda Mikāʾel</persName> are mentioned. 
                        To consult <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2375Synaxa#FirstHalf">No item: LIT2375Synaxa, could not check for FirstHalf</title> written by the same scribe, refer to <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdd013">ESdd013</ref>.
                      </origDate>
                  </origin>
                 
